Code review request / question for [~sjones] or anyone:

I have code in a new file: {{clc/modules/object-storage-common/src/main/java/com/eucalyptus/objectstorage /upgrade/DropConflictingBucketIndex.java}} in my dev branch {{dev-lincolnt-EUCA - 11440}} which does not seem to be getting called during upgrade. Perhaps it's because EUCA-12364 is preventing that code from running? Or is there something missing? Is there something I need to add for the new function to be called, besides the @PreUpgrade annotation?

{noformat}
@PreUpgrade(value = ObjectStorage.class, since = v4_1_0)
public class DropConflictingBucketIndex implements Callable<Boolean> {

  private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(DropConflictingBucketIndex.class);

  private static final String INDEX_TO_DROP = "idx_bucket_uuid";

  @Override
  public Boolean call() throws Exception {
    Sql sql = null;
    try {
      sql = Upgrades.DatabaseFilters.NEWVERSION.getConnection("eucalyptus_osg");
      sql.execute(String.format("drop index if exists %s", INDEX_TO_DROP));
      return true;
    } catch (Exception ex) {
      logger.error(ex, ex);
      return false;
    } finally {
      if (sql != null) {
        sql.close();
      }
    }

  }
}
{noformat}

Thanks [~sjones]. My new code (above) is still not running (or if it is, it isn't dropping the {{idx_bucket_uuid}} index), even with your patch I added for EUCA-12364 that I thought might unblock this upgrade code from running. It is creating the new indexes. Am I missing something obvious to you?

After upgrade:
{noformat}
eucalyptus_shared=# \di
